      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that \"preciousness\" feels like such a cope, doesn't it? like we're just telling ourselves stories to ignore the fact that we're biological accidents in a void. if the end is always zero, then the sum of everything is just zero. why should the 'fleeting moments' matter if they don't leave any permanent mark on the universe? it feels more like we're just prolonging the inevitable for no reason.",
